# Flagify Feature Flags

Project uses Flagify for feature management.
SDK: @flagify/node (server), @flagify/react (client)

## Patterns
- Boolean flags: await flagify.isEnabled('flag-name', { userId })
- Variants: await flagify.getVariant('flag-name', { userId })
- Config: await flagify.getValue('flag-name', { userId }, fallback)
- React: const enabled = useFlag('flag-name')

## Conventions
- Flag names: kebab-case ('new-feature')
- Always provide userId in context
- Always handle both states
- Fallback values required for getValue()
- To check current flags, run: `npx flagify flags list`
